{"key":"post-13452636","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13452636</id>\n<content>You want to pasteurize a casing mix, not sterilize.&amp;nbsp; This &lt;i&gt;prevents&lt;/i&gt; molds from getting a foothold.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Don't skip the lime.&amp;nbsp; If you do, the uncolonized parts of the casing mix are much more easily contaminated.&amp;nbsp; The best place to get hydrated lime is at a feed store, not a nursery.&amp;nbsp; You'll also want to pick up a bag of gypsum there as well.&amp;nbsp; Use gypsum at about 5% to the amount of your casing material.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13452657</next>\n<prev>13452626</prev>\n<first>13452162</first>\n<last>13543533</last>\n<when>1289229233</when>\n<utime>11/08/10 05:13 PM</utime>\n</post>"}